Global investors  bought a  net 8.04
billion rupees ($161.3 million) of Indian equity  derivatives 
March 9, according to the National Stock Exchange.  Open interest, or the number of contracts outstanding in
value terms, rose 4.3 percent to 909.2 billion rupees, or 35.6
percent of the gross market position, according to the
exchangeâ€™s website. Open interest reached a record 1.6 trillion
rupees on Sept. 21, 2010.  Foreign funds bought a net 12.85 billion rupees of shares
in the  cash  segment on March 9, according to preliminary data
given by the bourse.  To contact the reporter on this story:
